= The Raiders

'The Raiders flew over the battlefields and crashed headfirst into the enemy formations. They, with their rapid cavalry and light weaponry, massacred the enemy and built hills out of the skulls of the men they butchered and ran over. They sow fear and confusion among the infidels facing the Sublime State and the crescent of Islam shined over each puddle of blood spilt on every battlefield.'

The raiders ceased to be a thing over 150 years ago, with them being replaced by the modern Ottoman army which unlike the raiders moved with strategy instead of frency and prioritized controlledness over fanaticism.

Yet, the memory of the forgotten Ottoman troop is being revitalized at the hands of the MSP and the Islamist youth movements, being remanufactured and reimplemented to suit an era which had neither the need for such medieval troops nor their outdated tactics, but rather their fanaticism in order to foster a youth as devoted and as willing to die for the cause of Islam as the raiders originally were.

The glorification of the values of a long gone era is fundamental in all far right ideologies, and Islamists prove no different.

Have I told you the first paragraph is a reinterpretation?

